Durban - Quick police work led to the arrest of a man, in possession of an unlicensed firearm, who had just held up a resident for his laptop in KwaNdengezi on Tuesday. Police officers from KwaNdengezi SAPS were conducting duties at the Community Service Centre when a man arrived and reported to police that he was robbed of his laptop at gunpoint said Colonel Thembeka Mbele, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson. The victim provided police with a description of the suspect and the police officers immediately responded. "While searching the area the suspect was spotted walking along Tom Road. He was approached and upon searching him an unlicensed firearm and ammunition was found in his possession. The suspect directed police to a house where the complainant’s laptop was  recovered," Mbele said. The 25-year-old suspect was placed under arrest. He is expected to appear in the Pinetown Magistrates Court to face charges of possession of unlicensed firearm, ammunition as well as armed robbery. Daily News 